icler  Geoffrey  of Monmouth (  d. 1155 ). The original form and meaning of the name is disputed. According to one theory, it is merely a variant of   Godfrey ;  others derive the first part from the Germanic word <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Geoffrey de Sturmy had at least 1 son with Geoffrey De Sturmy."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1325–1381":"1325–1381","1356–1427":"1356–1427","–Female":"Surnud","1325":"1325","1356":"1356","1381":"1381","1427":"1427","Hall End, Warwickshire, England":"Hall End, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1325–1381":"1325–1381","1356–1427":"1356–1427","–Female":"Kuollut","1325":"1325","1356":"1356","1381":"1381","1427":"1427","Hall End, Warwickshire, England":"Hall End, Warwickshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1325–1381":"1325–1381","1356–1427":"1356–1427","–Female":"Décédée","1325":"1325","1356":"1356","1381":"1381","1427":"1427","Hall End, Warwickshire, England":"Hall End, Warwickshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs Geoffrey de Sturmy a eu au moins 1 fils avec Geoffrey De Sturmy."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1325–1381":"1325–1381","1356–1427":"1356–1427","–Female":"Verstorben","1325":"1325","1356":"1356","1381":"1381","1427":"1427","Hall End, Warwickshire, England":"Hall End, Warwickshire, England","lifeSummary":"Mrs Geoffrey de Sturmy hatte mit Geoffrey De Sturmy mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1325–1381":"1325–1381","1356–1427":"1356–1427","–Female":"Desede","1325":"1325","1356":"1356","1381":"1381","1427":"1427","Hall End, Warwickshire, England":"Hall End, Warwickshire, England"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1325–1381":"1325–1381","1356–1427":"1356–1427","–Female":"elhunyt","1325":"1325","1356":"1356","1381":"1381","1427":"1427","Hall End, Warwickshi